    "view": {
      "representation": "view",
      "value": "<h3 id=\"CurvesinMaya-MayaCurves\">Maya Curves</h3><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"894\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544539731/rfmMayaCurve.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431548502&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=697&amp;height=330\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544539731/rfmMayaCurve.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431548502&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"330\" data-width=\"697\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544539764\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"rfmMayaCurve.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544539731\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"0233350d-7c0a-436b-9e9c-30501ed1d2d6\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544539731/rfmMayaCurve.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431548502&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=697&amp;height=330 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544539731/rfmMayaCurve.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431548502&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=697&amp;height=330 1x\"></span><p>Maya curves can be tagged to be rendered.  Create curves with one of the curve tools under:</p><p style=\"margin-left: 30.0px;\">Create &gt; Curve Tools</p><p>In the Attribute Editor be sure and assign a material to your curves:</p><p /><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"683\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544539731/rfmMayaCurveAttrs.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431548673&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=482&amp;height=143\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544539731/rfmMayaCurveAttrs.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431548673&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"143\" data-width=\"482\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544539767\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"rfmMayaCurveAttrs.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544539731\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"5ad0acee-7f37-4971-a2f9-1324352c4c4b\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544539731/rfmMayaCurveAttrs.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431548673&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=482&amp;height=143 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544539731/rfmMayaCurveAttrs.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431548673&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=482&amp;height=143 1x\"></span><p /><p>That's it!  You should see the curve in your render.</p><p /><div class=\"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-information conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"6e57dd50-af88-4fbb-a9bc-b04d43bd7a49\" data-macro-name=\"info\"><span class=\"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info confluence-information-macro-icon\"> </span><div class=\"confluence-information-macro-body\"><p><span class=\"legacy-color-text-default\">For hair/fur curves: To use the IGS/Interactive Xgen surface UVs for color/texture, you can reference this in the PxrManifold2D of your color placement as scalpS and scalpT Primvars.</span></p></div></div><p /><p><strong>Ribbons</strong></p><p>By default, RenderMan renders curves as tubes, which is ideal for hair and fur.</p><p>For flat, ribbon style curves, the curve needs to be supplied with normals. Maya doesn't have this functionality out of the box, so there's a RenderMan-centric way to accomplish this via <a href=\"/wiki/spaces/RFM25/pages/21889359/About+Primitive+Variables\" data-linked-resource-id=\"21889359\" data-linked-resource-version=\"7\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">primvars</a>.</p><ul><li><p>Select the curve's shape node (select the curve in the outliner and press the down arrow).</p></li><li><p>Add a RenderMan primvar named rmanNN</p><ul><li><p>main menu &gt; Modify</p></li><li><p>Add Attribute...</p></li><li><p>Long Name = rmanNN</p></li><li><p>data Type = Vector</p></li></ul></li><li><p>Change rmanNN in the curve shape node to anything but 0, for example, 1, 0, 0.</p></li><li><p>This will supply the curve with a normal and twist the curve.</p></li></ul><p /><p><strong>Maya Scene &gt; </strong><a href=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/21037320/flat_curve.ma.zip?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1696377764177&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" rel=\"nofollow\"><strong>flat_curve.ma.zip</strong></a></p><p /><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"650\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544539731/flat-vs-tube-curves.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431548265&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=650&amp;height=365\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544539731/flat-vs-tube-curves.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431548265&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"540\" data-width=\"960\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544539749\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"flat-vs-tube-curves.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544539731\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"f5a1f486-5ada-4139-8ca6-1165f2a21d3b\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544539731/flat-vs-tube-curves.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431548265&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=960&amp;height=540 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544539731/flat-vs-tube-curves.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431548265&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=650&amp;height=365 1x\"></span><p /><div class=\"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-information conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"075e2cdd-7b91-4c34-aa00-472620387051\" data-macro-name=\"info\"><span class=\"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info confluence-information-macro-icon\"> </span><div class=\"confluence-information-macro-body\"><h3 id=\"CurvesinMaya-Primvars\">Primvars</h3><p>To learn more about RenderMan Primitive Variables in RenderMan for Maya, check out the About Primitive Variables page:</p><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://rmanwiki-26.pixar.com/space/RFM26/21037375/About+Primitive+Variables\" rel=\"nofollow\">Learn More</a></p></div></div><p />"
    }
